description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Come and achieve your nursing potential at Nottingham University Hospitals NHS Trust (NUH), rated ‘outstanding’ for caring by CQC, and the only organisation in Europe with ANCC Pathway to Excellence® and Magnet® recognised Hospitals. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Join us at our next recruitment event, find out more about our organisation where we are committed to international excellence in nursing care and patient outcomes.&lt;strong&gt;:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Nottingham University Hospitals (NUH) Band 5 Recruitment Day | &lt;strong&gt;Saturday 28th November 2020&lt;/strong&gt; | Venue to be confirmed&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Neonatal Service delivers critical care across two sites, the City and Queen&#39;s Medical Centre Campus. As lead centre in the Trent Perinatal Network, we offer both medical and surgical intensive care for extremely premature and very sick infants. We also have an integrated outreach team in place to support babies and families once they return home.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At the event you will have the opportunity to:&lt;br /&gt;• Meet your future colleagues&lt;br /&gt;• Have an interview on the day&lt;br /&gt;• Find out where your career can lead&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re now recruiting across all of our divisions. Please note this advert is for &lt;strong&gt;Neonates Nursing&lt;/strong&gt; only.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are interested in applying for - -&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Theatre Practitioner&lt;/strong&gt; - see vacancy 164-2730920&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Adult Nursing&lt;/strong&gt; - see vacancy 164-2730920&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Critical Care Nursing&lt;/strong&gt; - see vacancy 164-2730892-CC&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We also welcome international nurses wanting to join our successful OSCE Programme, who have completed language requirements, CBT part one and in receipt of an invitation from the NMC to sit the Test of Competence.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameJenny MachellJob titleWard SisterEmail addressjenny.machell@nuh.nhs.ukTelephone number0115 9691169 ext. 55155 or 76202Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Paul Farmer ext 84030&lt;/p&gt;
